The \C[6]Raven's Keep Sewer System\C[0] allows for extra water
pressure to be delivered to specific districts as needed.
Each "\C[6]Zone\C[0]" has its own control mechenism with the ability to
raise or lower the water available.
The central console shows the current pressure in each "Zone". When
a zone is operating at its default capacity, its pressure is "0".
Raising or lowering the water level in a zone will increase or
decrease, respectively, the pressure on the entire system.
A failsafe mechenism exists to ensure the system does not overload due
to pressure being too high or too low across the entire system.
Currently, all zones will reset to their neutral values if
the overall pressure raises above 20 or drops below -24.
Neutral pressure values for all zones are as follows:
NEVER lower the OVERALL pressure of the system to the EXACT
negative neutral pressure of a zone! A known glitch will
cause the entire zone to empty completely!
Example: \C[6]Zone 1\C[0] has a neutral pressure of
\C[6]5\C[0]. If the OVERALL pressure of the system is \C[6]-5\C[0] and
